  "prompt": "How do you remember which continents are located in the northern hemisphere?",
  "response": "To remember which continents are located in the Northern Hemisphere, you can use the following method: \n\n**Mnemonic:** \"Everyone Always Wants New Ants\"\n\nEach letter in the mnemonic corresponds to a continent located in the Northern Hemisphere:\n\n- **E**: Europe\n- **A**: Asia\n- **W**: (part of) Africa (around \u2153 of Africa is in the Northern Hemisphere)\n- **N**: North America\n- **A**: (part of) South America (a small portion of South America, primarily northern parts, falls in the Northern Hemisphere)\n\nUsing mnemonics can help make it easier to recall the continents that lie in the Northern Hemisphere. Moreover, it's important to remember that both Africa and South America straddle the equator, so parts of them are in both the Northern and Southern Hemispheres.",
